definition[0]: to wash the inside of something quickly
example[0]: I’ll just wash out this vase for flowers.
definition[1]: if a substance washes out, you can remove it from a material by washing it
example[1]: a dye that won’t wash out
definition[2]: if an event is washed out, it cannot continue because of rain
example[2]: The summer fair was washed out by the English weather.
